Careers



            To apply for opportunities, please send a cover letter and resume to: careers@investure.com


Investment Analyst  
The Investure Analyst program provides a broad introduction to institutional investing and portfolio
            management, including investment diligence and decision making. Investment Analysts provide a
            range of critical analytical support which includes working directly with the investment team on client
            presentations, data collection and processing, and portfolio and manager analytics. Work is initially
            comprised of internal analytical functions but ultimately progresses to be primarily investment
            diligence support. Throughout the program, Analysts will attend investment team meetings, work with
            senior members of the investment team, and gain exposure to world class investors. The ideal
            candidate will possess excellent academic credentials, strong excel skills, an interest in investing, and a
            natural focus on improvement. Investment Analysts must be detail-oriented, possess a high level of
            maturity, have a service mindset, and align with our Guiding Principles. The program is structured to
            be a 3 year commitment and we are currently seeking an Investment Analyst with 1-2 years of
            experience.
            
 Job Description


Administrative Assistant
This professional will be an integral member of Investure’s Human Resources & Administration Team reporting to the Director of the team. This position will be primarily responsible for duties pertaining to reception and facilities, travel assistance, and general administrative tasks.
            

